<Link id="l01400" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1400"><span class="doxyHighlight">            </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// value. Extend the lifetime of the new def point.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01401" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1401"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01402" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1402"><span class="doxyHighlight">            </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Extend to where the previous range started, unless there is</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01403" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1403"><span class="doxyHighlight">            </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// another redef first.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01404" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1404"><span class="doxyHighlight">            NewDefEndPoint = std::min(OldIdxIn-&gt;start,</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01405" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1405"><span class="doxyHighlight">                                      std::next(NewIdxOut)-&gt;start);</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01406" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1406"><span class="doxyHighlight">          &#125;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01407" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1407"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01408" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1408"><span class="doxyHighlight">          </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Merge the OldIdxIn and OldIdxOut segments into OldIdxOut.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01409" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1409"><span class="doxyHighlight">          OldIdxOut-&gt;valno-&gt;def = OldIdxIn-&gt;start;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01410" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1410"><span class="doxyHighlight">          &#42;OldIdxOut = LiveRange::Segment(OldIdxIn-&gt;start, OldIdxOut-&gt;end,</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01411" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1411"><span class="doxyHighlight">                                          OldIdxOut-&gt;valno);</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01412" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1412"><span class="doxyHighlight">          </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// OldIdxIn and OldIdxVNI are now undef and can be overridden.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01413" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1413"><span class="doxyHighlight">          </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// We Slide &#91;NewIdxIn, OldIdxIn) down one position.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01414" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1414"><span class="doxyHighlight">          </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//    |- X0/NewIdxIn -| ... |- Xn-1 -||- Xn/OldIdxIn -||- OldIdxOut -|</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l01416" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1416"><span class="doxyHighlight">          std::copy&#95;backward(NewIdxIn, OldIdxIn, OldIdxOut);</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01417" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1417"><span class="doxyHighlight">          </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// NewIdxIn is now considered undef so we can reuse it for the moved</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01418" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1418"><span class="doxyHighlight">          </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// value.</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l01420" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1420"><span class="doxyHighlight">          <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/liverange/#a143c1fcb6066cb301f828ec4c18d79f4">LiveRange::iterator</a> <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/#ab13c360340346d082b959b8cd79f2c1a">Next</a> = std::next(NewSegment);</span></CodeLine>
